The Minister of Natural Resources and Tourism, Dr. Damas Ndumbaro has asked pastoralists and people living around the National Parks in Chato district, Geita region not to bring back their livestock into the reserves with the purpose of environmental conservation. Dr. Ndumbaro said this, while inspecting the Biharamulo Tree Farm in the district, adding that once any herd is caught will be nationalized. Equally, he declared Chato District a center of conservation and tourism in the Lake Zone Region on grounds that it has several tourist attractions.